Destiny 2 will launch for Windows PC, PlayStation 4, and Xbox One on 8 September 2017. Gameplay for the new title is set to be shown off on 18 May. Bungie and Activision stated that there will also be a beta of the game before its official launch, with early access available to those who preorder the new FPS. The original Destiny was a massive hit with console gamers, and the sequel sees the game now available for PC owners – expanding its player base. The game’s reveal trailer is posted below. 